First, `select` is not needed for this.  And I prefer `COALESCE()` to `ISNULL()` (`COALESCE()` is standard SQL).

    @mainamount = coalesce(format(cast(sum(receipt_amount) as money), &#39;N&#39;, &#39;en-in&#39;), 0)

The problem is that the `0` specifies that the return type is a *number*.  When there is a type conflict, the more restrictive type is usually chosen -- that is, strings are converted to numbers and dates, when one has to be chosen.

But the `FORMAT()` is returning a string.  You can fix this just by have the alternative value be a string:

    @mainamount = coalesce(format(cast(sum(receipt_amount) as money), &#39;N&#39;, &#39;en-in&#39;), &#39;0&#39;)

